---
import FaqList from "../components/FaqList.astro";
import GuideLinks from "../components/GuideLinks.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { beginnerFaqs } from "../data/faqs";
import { lastCheckedLabel, pages } from "../data/site";

const page = pages.find((item) => item.pathname === "/wizard-alchemy-beginner-guide/")!;
---

<BaseLayout
  title={page.title}
  description={page.description}
  pathname="/wizard-alchemy-beginner-guide/"
  pageType="Article"
  faq={beginnerFaqs}
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="wrap hero-inner">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">New player route</p>
        <h1>Wizard Alchemy Beginner Guide</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          Start Wizard Alchemy with a clean route: redeem codes, finish the
          tutorial, collect materials, brew potions, unlock spells, and spend
          Race Rerolls only when you know what to keep.
        </p>
        <div class="meta-row">
          <span class="badge">Last updated: {lastCheckedLabel}</span>
          <span class="badge">MVP guide</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <aside class="hero-visual" aria-label="Beginner route">
        <p class="eyebrow">First hour</p>
        <ul class="quick-list">
          <li><span>Step 1</span><strong>Redeem codes</strong></li>
          <li><span>Step 2</span><strong>Finish tutorial</strong></li>
          <li><span>Step 3</span><strong>Collect materials</strong></li>
          <li><span>Step 4</span><strong>Brew potions</strong></li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap content-grid">
      <article class="prose">
        <h2>What Is Wizard Alchemy?</h2>
        <p>
          Wizard Alchemy is a Roblox progression game built around materials,
          potion crafting, spell unlocks, races, and combat. Your early goal is
          to build enough potion power to farm faster without wasting rerolls or
          rare materials.
        </p>

        <h2>First Things to Do After Joining</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Open the settings or utilities menu and redeem every working code.</li>
          <li>Check your race and compare it with the race tier list.</li>
          <li>Finish the tutorial prompts so every core menu is available.</li>
          <li>Gather low-risk materials before fighting harder enemies.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Redeem Codes First</h2>
        <p>
          The current codes give Race Rerolls, which matter most before you lock
          into longer farming sessions. Visit the <a href="/">Wizard Alchemy codes</a>
          page before every new play session.
        </p>

        <h2>Finish the Tutorial</h2>
        <p>
          Follow the early prompts until you can gather, brew, fight, and open
          the required menus. Do not judge the pacing until the alchemy table and
          spell flow are unlocked.
        </p>

        <h2>How to Collect Materials</h2>
        <p>
          Materials come from gathering nodes, enemies, bosses, and chests.
          Starter materials are useful because combining several low Magic Power
          items can still reach early potion targets.
        </p>

        <h2>How to Brew Your First Potion</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Collect a few starter materials.</li>
          <li>Open the Alchemy table.</li>
          <li>Add materials until the Magic Power reaches an early potion target.</li>
          <li>Brew the potion and use it to unlock or improve a spell.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>How to Unlock Spells</h2>
        <p>
          Potions are the bridge between materials and spells. If your build
          feels weak, the next useful upgrade is usually a better potion route,
          not a random reroll.
        </p>

        <h2>How to Use Race Rerolls</h2>
        <p>
          Reroll Human once you have free spins. Stop if you land an S tier or
          strong A tier race. If you land a B tier race, keep it until you have
          enough extra rerolls to chase a higher tier safely.
        </p>

        <h2>Early Game Farming Tips</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Keep elemental shards until you know which potion route you want.</li>
          <li>Use chests to fill gaps in your material inventory.</li>
          <li>Do not sell rare or high Magic Power materials just for quick cash.</li>
          <li>Upgrade around one or two spells instead of spreading resources thin.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Beginner Mistakes to Avoid</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Spending all Race Rerolls before checking the tier list.</li>
          <li>Selling materials before learning potion Magic Power targets.</li>
          <li>Ignoring chests when farming enemy drops.</li>
          <li>Trying to craft late-game potions with only starter materials.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Next Guides to Read</h2>
        <GuideLinks />
      </article>
      <aside class="aside">
        <h2>Beginner Priority</h2>
        <p>
          Redeem codes first, then decide whether to keep your race. After that,
          focus on potions and materials.
        </p>
        <p><a href="/wizard-alchemy-race-tier-list/">Check race tier list</a></p>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <FaqList items={beginnerFaqs} />
</BaseLayout>
